TUCKER v. CRAWFORDSVILLE STATE BANK. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. January 24, 1917.) No. 2949. In Error to the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of Florida; Rhydon M. Call, Judge. J. C. Davant, of Brooksville, Fla., for plaintiff in error. Peter O. Knight, of Tampa, Fla., for defendant in error.

Before PARDEE and WALKER, Circuit Judges, and GRUBB, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

We find none of the assignments of error well taken. The judgment of the District Court is affirmed.
